# 🔁 DigiCert ONE – Full Automation via Shell Script

## 🔐 Prerequisites (set once)

```bash
export DCONE_URL="https://<your-digicert-one-host>"
export API_TOKEN="YOUR_API_TOKEN"
export PROFILE_ID="PROFILE_UUID"
```

---

## 1️⃣ Generate Private Key + CSR (OpenSSL)

```bash
CN="example.com"
KEY_FILE="server.key"
CSR_FILE="server.csr"

openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes \
  -keyout "$KEY_FILE" \
  -out "$CSR_FILE" \
  -subj "/CN=${CN}"
```

---

## 2️⃣ Submit Certificate Request

```bash
CSR_CONTENT=$(awk '{printf "%s\\n", $0}' "$CSR_FILE")

REQUEST_ID=$(curl -sk -X POST \
  "$DCONE_URL/rest/v1/certificaterequests" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{
    \"profileId\": \"$PROFILE_ID\",
    \"csr\": \"$CSR_CONTENT\",
    \"validityPeriod\": {
      \"unit\": \"DAYS\",
      \"value\": 365
    }
  }" | jq -r '.id')

echo "Certificate Request ID: $REQUEST_ID"
```

✅ Requires `jq` (`yum install jq` or `apt install jq`)

---

## 3️⃣ Poll Until Certificate Is Issued

```bash
echo "Waiting for certificate issuance..."

while true; do
  RESPONSE=$(curl -sk \
    "$DCONE_URL/rest/v1/certificaterequests/$REQUEST_ID" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_TOKEN")

  STATUS=$(echo "$RESPONSE" | jq -r '.status')

  echo "Status: $STATUS"

  if [ "$STATUS" = "ISSUED" ]; then
    CERT_ID=$(echo "$RESPONSE" | jq -r '.certificateId')
    break
  fi

  if [ "$STATUS" = "REJECTED" ]; then
    echo "❌ Certificate request rejected"
    exit 1
  fi

  sleep 10
done

echo "Certificate ID: $CERT_ID"
```

---

## 4️⃣ Download the Certificate (PEM + Chain)

```bash
curl -sk \
  "$DCONE_URL/rest/v1/certificates/$CERT_ID/download?format=PEM&includeChain=true" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_TOKEN" \
  -o server.crt
```

Result:

```
server.key   (private key)
server.crt   (certificate + chain)
```

---

## 5️⃣ Install & Reload Service (Example: NGINX)

```bash
cp server.key /etc/nginx/ssl/server.key
cp server.crt /etc/nginx/ssl/server.crt

nginx -t && systemctl reload nginx
```

---

## 6️⃣ Automatic Renewal (Cron Example)

Renew **30 days before expiry**:

```bash
CERT_FILE="/etc/nginx/ssl/server.crt"
DAYS_LEFT=$(openssl x509 -enddate -noout -in "$CERT_FILE" | \
  cut -d= -f2 | \
  xargs -I{} date -d "{}" +%s | \
  awk '{print int(($1 - systime()) / 86400)}')

if [ "$DAYS_LEFT" -le 30 ]; then
  echo "Renewing certificate..."
  /path/to/renew.sh
fi
```

Cron entry:

```bash
0 2 * * * /path/to/check-and-renew.sh
```

